The problem is not with the delegate, but with the recursion:

1. Example.toString() is called
2. Delegate.getValue() is called by `$p`. An instance of Example is passed to getValue.
3. Example.toString() is called by `$thisRef`. So it loops back to step 1!!

You can reproduce the same with this very simple example:

```kotlin
fun main() {
    class SimpleExample {
        override fun toString() = &quot;$this&quot;
    }

    println(SimpleExample())
}
```

In order to fix it, remove the `$thisRef` from the `getValue` function.

